  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As part of #3045, we need a way to store archival state data for retrieval during API requests, such as users wanting to know the historical assignments of validators at a certain epoch. For this purpose, we should store as minimal data as possible and gate this functionality behind a feature flag.  This would unblock us from finishing #3045 and add a lot of utility to our beacon nodes for block explorers such as [Mytchmatic](https://twitter.com/preston_vanloon/status/1148977073660321793).\r\n\r\nOpening this issue up as this would require a design document before we start work.",
